-- Kenya's British American to List in Nairobi by June 30, Seeks $74 Million
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2011-02-10T14:33:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-10/kenya-s-british-american-to-list-in-nairobi-by-june-30-seeks-74-million.html
British American Investments Co.  Kenya  Ltd., the holding company of  British American Insurance
Co. , plans to start trading its shares in Nairobi by the end of
June, Group Managing Director Benson Wairegi said.  The company plans to raise from 6 billion shillings ($74
million) to 7 billion shillings, Wairegi told reporters today in
the capital, Nairobi.  “Having recently opened operations in Uganda, our
strategic intent is to spread our wings even further to the rest
of East Africa,” he said. Britak, as the company is known,
plans to operate in  Tanzania , Rwanda, Burundi and  Southern Sudan 
in addition to Kenya and  Uganda , Wairegi said. It is also
interested in property development, he said.  Britak, which began operations in Kenya in 1965, will
become the third insurer to be listed on the Nairobi Stock
Exchange after  Jubilee Holdings Ltd ., which has operations in
Kenya, Tanzania, Burundi and Mauritius, and  Pan Africa Insurance
Holdings Ltd ., a unit of South Africa’s Sanlam Ltd.  The company, which is 37 percent owned by British-American
Insurance Co. Mauritius Ltd., said  profit  before tax climbed 35
percent to 504 million shillings in the 12 months to December
2009, according to its annual report. Gross premiums were 3.8
billion shillings with assets worth 16 billion shillings at the
end of December 2009, it added.  Total premiums in Kenya increased to 55 billion shillings
in 2009 from 48 billion shillings a year earlier, it said. With
300 employees and 750 agents, the company’s investment income
was more than 200 million shillings at the end of 2009, Britak
said.  CFC Insurance Holdings Ltd., a unit of CFC Stanbic
Holdings, received regulatory approval to sell shares on the
Kenyan stock exchange, it said on Nov. 15.  To contact the reporter on this story:
